# PATCH 006: Antigravity anti-fingerprinting on top of upstream version updates
#
# Builds on upstreams Antigravity release updater instead of shadowing it locally.
# Keeps the fork-specific fingerprinting improvements that upstream still lacks:
#
# 1. Session ID: salt with auth ID and emit the structured real-traffic shape
#    (-{uuid}:{model}:{project}:seed-{hex16}) to reduce cross-account correlation.
# 2. User-Agent: keep the upstream version source, but choose a deterministic
#    per-account platform fingerprint and prevent version downgrades per account.
# 3. Project ID: expand the adjective/noun pools for more realistic random names.

diff --git a/internal/runtime/executor/antigravity_executor.go b/internal/runtime/executor/antigravity_executor.go
